		 Moon 		 
 
		 
			 Posted on  February 11, 2014 February 10, 2018  by  Dave Addey 		 
		 
			 After studying  2001: A Space Odyssey  in intimate detail , Duncan Jones’s  Moon  was the logical choice for my second foray into sci-fi typography. As its opening shot illustrates,  Moon  is a bleak, lonely, and above all  beautiful  love-letter to classic sci-fi typography and design. It’s also one of my favorite sci-fi films of all time. 
 
 UPDATE:  I forgot to mention it originally, but this article contains some pretty massive spoilers about the plot of  Moon . In my defense, you’re here to read about typography, and typography is  always  essential to the plot. Nonetheless, if you haven’t seen  Moon ,  go and watch it first . The future will still be here when you’re 